# =============================================================
# FRONTEND ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES — CSA Kirinyaga Church Website
# =============================================================
#
# HOW TO USE:
#   1. Copy this file and rename it to ".env" (remove the .example)
#   2. Fill in the values below for your local machine
#   3. NEVER commit your actual .env file to GitHub — it is in .gitignore
#
# =============================================================

# -----------------------------------------------
# VITE_SERVER_URI  (REQUIRED)
# -----------------------------------------------
# This is the URL where your backend server is running.
#
# WHY IS THIS NEEDED?
#   Vite (the frontend dev tool) runs on port 5173 by default.
#   The backend (Node/Express) runs on a DIFFERENT port — 3001.
#
#   When the Donate button is clicked, the frontend needs to send
#   an M-Pesa STK Push request to the backend. Without this variable,
#   the request goes to port 5173 (the frontend itself) instead of
#   port 3001 (the backend), causing a 404 Not Found error.
#
#   This variable tells the frontend: "Hey, when making API calls,
#   send them to http://localhost:3001, not to yourself."
#
# FOR LOCAL DEVELOPMENT:
VITE_SERVER_URI=http://localhost:3001
#
# FOR PRODUCTION (when deployed):
#   Change this to your actual backend domain, e.g.:
#   VITE_SERVER_URI=https://api.yourdomain.com
#
# =============================================================
